data.text:
Cameron Jibril Thomaz (born: September 8, 1987 (1987-09-08) [age 36]), better known professionally as Wiz Khalifa, is an American musician, rapper, and songwriter, who performs the genres of rap, pop rap, hip hop, and trap.

Music[]

Since he began his career in 2005, he's released a total of six studio albums, including:

Show and Prove, (2006)

Deal or No Deal, (2009)

Rolling Papers, (2011)

O.N.I.F.C., (2012)

Blacc Hollywood, (2014)

Rolling Papers 2, (2018)

24 mixtapes:

Prince of the City: Welcome to Pistolvania, (2005)

Grow Session, (2007)

Prince of the City 2, (2007)

Star Power, (2008)

Flight School, (2009)

How Fly (with Currensy), (2009)

Burn After Rolling, (2009)

Kush & Orange Juice, (2010)

Cabin Fever, (2011)

Taylor Allderdice, (2012)

Cabin Fever 2, (2012)

28 Grams, (2014)

Cabin Fever 3, (2015)

TGOD Volume 1, (2016)

Pre-Rolleds, (2017)

Bong Rips, (2017)

Laugh Now, Fly Later, (2017)

Fly Times, Vol.1: The Good Fly Young, (2019)

It's Only Weed Bro, (2020)

3 Doobies, (2020)

Big Pimpin', (2020)

Just A Regular Day, (2020)

#FUCC2020, (2021)

Taylor Nights, (2021)

Three extended plays

Live in Concert (with Curren$y), (2013)

Talk About It in the Morning (with Ty Dolla Sign), (2015)

The Saga of Wiz Khalifa, (2020).

Two collaborative albums:

Rude Awakening (with Juicy J & TM88; as TGOD Mafia), (2016)

2009 (with Curren$y), (2019)

A compilation album: Khalifa, (2016) and a soundtrack album: Mac & Devin Go to High School (with Snoop Dogg), (2011)
